div1.p: In the District Court, Of the third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the County of King.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of I H Smith by uou imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said I. H. Smith shall be called or chargerd, before the HON. Thomas Burke RICHARD A. JONES Judge of the aforesaid Court at in the Court room at the Court House in the City of Seattle W. T. on the 9th day of Feby A D 1889 at the hour of 4 o clock P.M. of said day to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning him the same I. H. Smith And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. Thomas Burke RICHARD A. JONES Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 9th day of February A. D. 1889. W. E. Ledgerwood Clerk. By H T Harmon Deputy Clerk.

E T No. 6550
In the District Court, Third Judicial District, Holding Terms at Seattle, W. T. In the Matter of the Application I. H. Smith For Writ of Habeas Corpus.
HABEAS CORPUS.
Returned and filed this 9th day of February A. D. 1889 W E Ledgerwood Clerk. By H T Harmon Deputy Clerk.
